Class AbstractModule

  • java.lang.Object
    • nl.uu.cs.ape.sat.models.logic.constructs.TaxonomyPredicate
      • nl.uu.cs.ape.sat.models.AbstractModule
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Predicate
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Module

    public class AbstractModule
extends TaxonomyPredicate
    The AbstractModule class represents modules/tools provided by the Module Taxonomy as well as their abstraction classes. Instances of AbstractModule can be actual tools or their abstraction classes, while all instances of the actual tools are extended to Module.
    Author:
    Vedran Kasalica

      • generateModule

        public static AbstractModule generateModule(java.lang.String moduleName,
                                            java.lang.String moduleID,
                                            java.lang.String rootNode,
                                            NodeType nodeType,
                                            AllModules allModules,
                                            AbstractModule superModule)
        The class is used to check weather the module with @moduleID was already introduced earlier on in @allModules. In case it was it returns the item, otherwise the new element is generated and returned.

        In case of generating a new Module, the object is added to the set of all the Modules and added as a subModule to the parent Module.
        Parameters:
        moduleName - - module name
        moduleID - - unique module identifier
        rootNode - - ID of the Taxonomy Root node corresponding to the Module.
        nodeType - - NodeType object describing the type w.r.t. the Module Taxonomy.
        allModules - - set of all the modules created so far
        superModule - - The Parent AbstractModule of the current Module
        Returns:
        the Abstract Module representing the item.
